==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydramine
<hw>Hy*dram"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydr</ets>oxyl + <ets>amine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a series of artificial, organic bases, usually produced as
thick viscous liquids by the action of ammonia on ethylene oxide. They
have the properties both of alcohol and amines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hydrangea</ent>⟦br⟧
